  "version": 1,
  "id": "hardclipping",
  "name": "Hard Clipping",
  "description": "Op-amp gain stage driving 1N914 silicon diodes shunting to ground. The amplified signal slams into the diodes and gets clamped at ±0.7V — producing flat-topped, aggressive distortion like a RAT or DS-1.",
